-Stay calm.
-What's going on?

16:36.960 --> 16:38.120
For the beginning...

16:38.440 --> 16:40.160
I think he interprets
for you.  Sit up.

16:40.280 --> 16:41.840
Incredible.  It looks like her.

16:42.360 --> 16:44.400
She doesn't take a day off,
not even after an accident.

16:44.560 --> 16:46.000
... more and more
market dominance?

16:47.280 --> 16:50.800
I would start with why
mergers save money.

16:51.600 --> 16:54.680
Mass production,
synergy effects, reduced

16:54.800 --> 16:58.880
development costs and
reduced product range.

16:59.360 --> 17:00.800
And she obviously
doesn't need me.

17:02.200 --> 17:04.440
-This is our fate, isn't it?
-Our fate?

17:05.240 --> 17:06.359
When we work for others, we

17:06.480 --> 17:08.359
consider our
relationship personal.

17:11.520 --> 17:13.520
I only work for the patients.

17:23.280 --> 17:26.160
I got your three pings.
Everything is unchanged.

17:26.280 --> 17:27.240
She is stable...

17:27.440 --> 17:28.640
How long have you
known about Guthrie?

17:29.400 --> 17:32.440
I stepped in and
intervened immediately...

17:32.560 --> 17:33.880
Is Malaya the only
one who knows?

17:34.640 --> 17:35.600
OK...

17:36.360 --> 17:37.520
I'm not getting into that.

17:37.920 --> 17:39.720
You are troubled, emotional,
now is the wrong time.

17:39.840 --> 17:42.880
Malaya Pineda is suspended.
From now on.

17:43.160 --> 17:44.800
-What?
-My daughter, Leanne!

17:45.120 --> 17:46.720
Is that Emily's father speaking?

17:47.320 --> 17:50.080
Because I thought I was talking
to the emergency room chief.

17:57.080 --> 17:59.080
I took ibuprofen
against it, but...

17:59.200 --> 18:00.520
When was the last
time this was examined?

18:00.880 --> 18:02.520
The military is
so bureaucratic...

18:02.680 --> 18:05.000
Dr.  Savetti, Dr.  Kean,
you already know my CO.

18:05.240 --> 18:06.800
I told them about the
bullet in my arm and that

18:06.920 --> 18:09.400
it reminded me that
shooting yourself hurts too.

18:09.520 --> 18:12.480
He had an untreated
skull fracture for years.

18:12.880 --> 18:15.080
He shows partial
mobility and numbness.

18:16.200 --> 18:17.160
Do you have pain?

18:17.880 --> 18:21.040
As always, I said
I take ibuprofen...

18:21.520 --> 18:24.160
-I can give something stronger.
-I said I'm fine.

18:24.880 --> 18:26.040
Let us help you.

18:27.120 --> 18:28.080
OK.

18:28.200 --> 18:31.200
I'll fill out this order,
but you'll get an MRI.

18:31.400 --> 18:33.480
-An MRI?
-That's my job.

18:34.280 --> 18:35.240
Let me help you.

18:36.680 --> 18:37.640
OK.

18:37.960 --> 18:41.440
-Good.  Should i follow
-General?  Who is the doctor

18:41.880 --> 18:43.760
-I want to send him something...
-The what?

18:44.120 --> 18:45.120
The doctor with the triplets.

18:45.400 --> 18:48.760
Oh, Henderson.  Harrison.
Something with H. I'll find out.

18:54.800 --> 18:57.120
You have a duty to the hospital.

18:57.240 --> 18:58.880
And now you wanna
tell me how to work

18:59.000 --> 19:00.840
I'm telling you that
Campbell's daughter has

19:00.960 --> 19:02.560
been endangered and
that was unnecessary.

19:02.680 --> 19:03.680
Do you think i don't know

19:07.120 --> 19:08.080
Why didn't you say it

19:10.680 --> 19:12.080
Because I had that under control.

19:12.200 --> 19:14.240
That's not how we work
here, and you know it.

19:14.800 --> 19:17.960
I made a mistake.
But it was mine

19:18.200 --> 19:20.280
and it has nothing
to do with you.

19:20.560 --> 19:23.080
-You are my right hand.
-I have my own hands.

19:23.240 --> 19:25.640
I am not an assistant.
I am a nurse.

19:28.880 --> 19:29.840
Is everything okay

19:32.000 --> 19:33.280
Yes, it's all fine.

19:34.520 --> 19:35.480
Forgiveness.

19:37.160 --> 19:38.120
My CO is here.

19:41.480 --> 19:43.200
He says he can send
me back to Afghanistan.

19:44.840 --> 19:47.240
-When?
-In a week.

19:52.120 --> 19:54.040
He is supposed to go to follow-up
care and do a complete blood count.

19:54.880 --> 19:55.840
Can I talk to you?

19:57.360 --> 19:58.320
No.

19:58.440 --> 20:00.320
There are rules about
what you are up to.

20:00.440 --> 20:03.960
And I'm in charge of surgery.
I will enforce it or not.

20:04.240 --> 20:05.760
When did you want to tell
me you have a daughter

20:05.880 --> 20:07.080
I didn't intend to.

20:07.280 --> 20:09.560
Is that why you never stayed
overnight when we were together?

20:11.400 --> 20:12.360
We weren't together.

20:15.680 --> 20:17.400
Well wait a minute.

20:19.160 --> 20:21.560
Please keep calm, I
need to do more tests.

20:22.960 --> 20:25.920
It might hurt for a moment, but
wait a minute... wait a minute.

20:28.760 --> 20:30.880
Stop, please, stop!

20:31.720 --> 20:33.400
I understand that
you are scared.

20:33.520 --> 20:36.280
I'm not afraid.  I just don't
want that.  I've had enough.

20:36.400 --> 20:37.760
-Sweet, sweetie...
-OK.

20:38.600 --> 20:39.560
Stop it.

20:40.320 --> 20:42.640
I'll sing Ave Maria at
the concert next week.

20:42.840 --> 20:44.400
I don't do anything else.

20:48.720 --> 20:49.680
Fine

20:54.320 --> 20:56.360
-It's my first solo...
-I know.

20:57.040 --> 20:58.480
Do you know what we do now

20:59.360 --> 21:00.600
I dont do this.  You do it.

21:03.040 --> 21:04.320
How about we do it together

21:05.160 --> 21:06.120
Give me your hand.

21:07.080 --> 21:08.040
There you are.

21:09.480 --> 21:11.720
We hold our anger in our hands

21:13.760 --> 21:16.200
and we'll look at
them very carefully.

21:16.760 --> 21:18.560
This is how we find
out what it really is.

21:19.960 --> 21:22.320
What is she honey  Come over.

21:27.440 --> 21:28.400
What do we see?

21:31.000 --> 21:32.200
It will never go away.

21:36.160 --> 21:37.120
OK.

21:39.200 --> 21:40.640
Now that we know
what the anger is

21:43.240 --> 21:44.520
what do we ask ourselves then?

21:46.600 --> 21:47.840
Will she help us?

21:49.480 --> 21:50.440
Exactly.

21:51.160 --> 21:53.320
And does she help us?

21:55.200 --> 21:56.400
-No she does not.
-No.

22:02.160 --> 22:03.120
So what do we do now?

22:04.400 --> 22:05.360
Let go of you.

22:05.960 --> 22:06.920
Let go of you.

22:07.640 --> 22:09.080
Like a bird that
flies in the sky.

22:09.840 --> 22:11.080
Like a bird that
flies in the sky.

22:13.040 --> 22:14.360
Exactly, this is my girl.

22:17.600 --> 22:18.560
It's fine baby

22:27.520 --> 22:29.760
-He suspended her.
-What?  Who?

22:29.880 --> 22:30.840
Malaya.

22:32.200 --> 22:33.160
For what?

22:33.280 --> 22:35.520
Because she knew about
Guthrie and didn't say anything.

22:36.560 --> 22:37.560
Like us.

22:38.400 --> 22:39.480
Campbell doesn't
know that, does he?

22:39.600 --> 22:41.480
The only difference between
us and Malaya is that...

22:41.600 --> 22:42.560
Slow down.

22:42.680 --> 22:44.040
-... had the courage to say something.
-So what?

22:44.160 --> 22:45.120
We should have helped her.

22:45.240 --> 22:47.240
You want to go to Campbell
so he can suspend us too?

22:47.760 --> 22:50.480
-We're talking about our career.
-We're talking about our girlfriend.

22:55.760 --> 22:57.640
There was an empty bed.
I should embarrass them.

22:57.880 --> 22:58.880
Naturally.

23:02.680 --> 23:05.640
"I'll postpone everything until next
week until then everything will be okay."

23:05.840 --> 23:06.960
Say I can't.

23:07.320 --> 23:09.520
I think I should
stay out of that.

23:09.640 --> 23:11.720
-I can raise you up to...
-Show her that.

23:14.640 --> 23:17.080
An email from Andy Singer.

23:17.280 --> 23:19.320
He said you were looking
for a replacement for me.

23:20.360 --> 23:24.040
You are not allowed to cancel the
trip because of your responsibility.

23:24.640 --> 23:27.520
Oversensitive?  We had
an accident two hours ago.

23:27.640 --> 23:29.320
Are you already looking
for a replacement for me?

23:34.280 --> 23:37.080
-I should have closed that.
-Moment.  I am so sorry.

23:38.840 --> 23:40.120
I wasn't ready to say it yet.

23:41.400 --> 23:44.320
Yes, that's why I
passed out in the car.

23:45.600 --> 23:48.080
I wanted to tell you.  No!  I...

23:49.400 --> 23:51.880
Stop!  Leave that open.
You don't have to do that.

23:52.640 --> 23:53.600
Moment!

23:57.240 --> 23:58.200
Can you tell her...

24:07.160 --> 24:09.520
Campbell, the man is with us

24:10.240 --> 24:12.520
and one of us... for decades.

24:13.120 --> 24:15.000
The people are the
heart of this place.

24:15.120 --> 24:18.520
They give everything every
day, every shift, every case.

24:20.080 --> 24:21.680
Guthrie is the Angels.

24:22.440 --> 24:24.520
Even so, you couldn't
fire him fast enough.

24:25.240 --> 24:26.240
I didn't fire him

24:28.760 --> 24:29.760
he resigned.

24:34.920 --> 24:37.040
I once ran about 30 km through

24:37.160 --> 24:39.320
the Hindu Kush
with a broken thigh.

24:39.760 --> 24:40.960
Sorry, hospital rules.

24:41.560 --> 24:44.160
Have you never been to the orthopedic
surgeon?  How long have you been hurt?

24:44.280 --> 24:47.400
Since Kandahar four years
ago, with medication, it's okay.

24:49.040 --> 24:51.160
-Don't you want water?
-That's okay.

24:51.680 --> 24:54.400
If you take them like
that, they work faster.

24:54.520 --> 24:55.480
Right?

24:55.640 --> 24:57.400
You don't always have clear
water when you're working.

24:57.520 --> 24:58.560
But they taste disgusting.

24:59.240 --> 25:01.360
Nobody would chew them like
that, only in an absolute emergency.

25:01.800 --> 25:02.800
Mario.

25:04.040 --> 25:06.520
That's true.  Small
dogs bark the loudest.

25:07.040 --> 25:08.560
What?  Do you think they are tough

25:08.680 --> 25:10.800
with your little pajamas
and teenage tattoos?

25:11.880 --> 25:14.240
You wouldn't know
if it kicked your ass.

25:14.440 --> 25:16.520
But keep up the good
work, maybe we can find out.

25:16.760 --> 25:18.320
And what kind of
games are you playing?

25:19.040 --> 25:21.360
Four years of narcotics and
you haven't seen a doctor?

25:21.880 --> 25:23.600
It sounds to me like
you don't want to get well.

25:23.720 --> 25:25.240
- Excuse me?
-Dr.  Savetti.

25:26.160 --> 25:27.280
Dr.  Kean, we'll be right there.

25:30.160 --> 25:31.880
-What are you doing?
-Help my patient.

25:32.040 --> 25:33.000
He's not your patient.

25:33.120 --> 25:36.320
I don't give prescriptions to
friends, colleagues or the boss.

25:36.520 --> 25:37.480
Pay attention.

25:37.760 --> 25:40.640
Like it or not, your
general has a problem.

25:41.360 --> 25:42.320
It's not just his shoulder.

25:42.440 --> 25:45.160
An injury like this can
cost him his career.

25:45.320 --> 25:47.120
Put it out of service
and then live with it.

25:47.520 --> 25:49.280
-This is your style.
-This is your diagnosis?

25:49.560 --> 25:50.680
An acute case of denial?

25:50.800 --> 25:52.320
Do you have any idea what
the man was going through?

25:52.640 --> 25:53.840
What each of us went through?

25:53.960 --> 25:56.440
No, but I do
recognize addictions.

25:56.600 --> 25:57.880
Dr.  Willis, come quickly.

25:58.320 --> 25:59.840
-The pulse is weak.
-Get him out.

25:59.960 --> 26:01.680
-He is unconscious.
-He's not breathing.

26:01.800 --> 26:03.200
Dr.  Savetti, the emergency vehicle.

26:07.040 --> 26:08.560
That was it.
There are only two left.

26:09.440 --> 26:10.560
How many have you
prescribed for him?

26:10.760 --> 26:13.720
Twelve.  He's overdosed.
Two milligrams of naloxone.

26:13.960 --> 26:14.920
All right.

26:16.800 --> 26:17.760
It's entered.

26:39.760 --> 26:41.960
-Thank you for being there.
-For Emily anytime.

26:42.280 --> 26:43.720
-I have to change my clothes.
-Good.

26:44.280 --> 26:47.240
Did you check that there is no
cell dividing cyst on the shunt?

26:47.360 --> 26:48.320
We excluded that.

26:49.240 --> 26:50.760
Then go.  Good.

26:53.320 --> 26:56.360
Dr.  Fields is L.A.'s most
respected pediatric neurosurgeon

26:57.000 --> 26:58.000
Yes.

26:58.160 --> 27:01.040
-She is in good hands.
-I just want to be able to trust.

27:02.320 --> 27:03.680
That's why you get
ready for the operation.

27:07.160 --> 27:09.880
I told her, but she
doesn't listen to me.

27:10.800 --> 27:13.520
I would prefer you to stay a

27:13.640 --> 27:14.960
little longer so
we can watch you.

27:15.200 --> 27:17.200
-"I have to work again."
-OK.

27:17.680 --> 27:19.240
I'm getting your
discharge papers ready.

27:37.720 --> 27:40.600
His heart is healthy.
Why is he not responding?

27:43.120 --> 27:46.320
Leanne, his QT times are up.

27:49.600 --> 27:51.520
I think he has hypocalcemia.

27:52.400 --> 27:54.880
It has to be.
Bone metastases from cancer.

27:55.040 --> 27:56.000
Give him calcium.

28:12.720 --> 28:14.360
-Looks like a sine wave.
-OK.

28:15.000 --> 28:17.960
Give him an infusion
at 1 mg per kg per hour.

28:18.080 --> 28:20.960
Check for anionized
calcium every 30 minutes.

28:22.000 --> 28:23.000
Mummy.

28:24.280 --> 28:26.640
Jesse, thank you.

28:28.480 --> 28:29.520
Mummy.

28:30.920 --> 28:31.880
All right.

28:42.800 --> 28:43.960
Tweezers.

28:51.280 --> 28:52.520
It won't come out.

28:52.760 --> 28:56.160
Sometimes the catheter
is scarred.  Just drag.

28:58.640 --> 28:59.680
Here you go.

29:02.200 --> 29:03.200
Suction.

29:07.640 --> 29:09.800
She was born with a dimple
at the end of the spine.

29:11.560 --> 29:12.520
This is how it begins.

29:14.440 --> 29:18.640
We were told that she would
never go and would soon die.

29:21.640 --> 29:24.480
My wife couldn't
stand it and left us.

29:25.680 --> 29:26.640
They are alone?

29:28.000 --> 29:28.960
As a couple.

29:30.520 --> 29:34.000
Emily and me.
We'll get through this together.

29:36.720 --> 29:38.440
She is bound to a wheelchair.

29:38.600 --> 29:42.320
She has neither bladder
nor bowel function.

29:44.680 --> 29:46.600
She must be catheterized
every three hours.

29:48.160 --> 29:49.760
She's been doing this
alone since she was four.

29:55.360 --> 29:57.520
We live our life in
3-hour segments.

30:00.000 --> 30:02.000
There is no light at
the end of the tunnel.

30:03.800 --> 30:08.400
Only she... She is...
She is the light.

30:10.480 --> 30:11.440
Yes that's her.

30:12.680 --> 30:14.560
But she wants to
be a normal kid.

30:15.880 --> 30:17.280
And that means that
she makes mistakes.

30:20.400 --> 30:22.480
If she makes mistakes,
she ends up here.
